# Additional data cleaning
shs_data <- shs_data %>% 
  select(-age) %>% # over 55000 NAs 
  mutate(across(where(is_character), str_to_sentence)) %>% 
  mutate(feature_name = str_to_title(feature_name)) %>% 
  mutate(measure = str_replace_all(measure, "_", " ")) %>% 
  rename(year = date_code)

Group variables            None

The data is aggregated from several datasets, covering 2013-2019 (year). The percent column is an estimate of the percentage of respondents that answered the survey. The measure column represents what factor is being measured. response relates to the response to a particular question (aka measure) from the SHS. feature_name, feature_code and feature_type all correspond to the location of the respondent. urban_rural_classification classifiers the area of a respondent as either being rural or urban. gender can either be “Male” or “Female”. household_type refers to who lives in the property, “Adults”, “Pensioners” or “With children”. type_of_tenure captures whether the property is “Owned”, “Owned mortgage/loan”, “Private rented”, “Social rented” or “Other”. SIMD_quintiles includes the top and lower 20% of the deprivation scale. ethnicity records the ethnicity of respondents as either “White” or “Other”. walking_distance_to_nearest_greenspace refers to the distance respondents have to walk to greenspace. NAs are present where data in the measure column relates to distance to greenspace.
Data is aggregated across all columns to include “All” levels.

   filter(measure == "Neighbourhood rating") %>% 
           urban_rural_classification == "Urban" |

Changes over time

Community Belonging

shs_data %>% 
  filter(measure == "Community belonging") %>%
  filter(
    gender == "All" &
      urban_rural_classification == "All" &
      simd_quintiles == "All" &
      type_of_tenure  == "All" &
      household_type  == "All" &
      ethnicity == "All" &
      walking_distance_to_nearest_greenspace == "All") %>% 
  mutate(response = factor(response, 
                           ordered = TRUE,
                           levels = c("Very strongly",
                                      "Fairly strongly", 
                                      "Don't know",
                                      "Not very strongly",
                                      "Not at all strongly"))) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = year, y = percent, colour = response)) +
  geom_line() +
  scale_colour_brewer(palette = "BrBG") +
  #scale_color_manual(values = c("deepskyblue4", "darkslategray3", "darkgreen", "darkolivegreen", "darkblue")) +
  facet_wrap(~feature_name) +
   labs(title = "Community belonging over time",
       subtitle = "Scotland 2013-2019",
       x = "Year",
       y = "Percentage") +
  guides(fill = guide_legend(title = "Rating"))
